<h3 id="how-it-started">How it started</h3>
<p>I started the channel as a passion project. A few years earlier I’d been hired as a teacher, and as much as I loved it, I only taught intro to web development classes, along with typography and page layout. I was missing something.</p>

<p>I wanted something that would let me be creative and push me to keep relevant, so after thinking about it for a
  <em>really</em>
  long time, I started my channel in October of 2016.</p>

<h3 id="progress-was-slow">Progress was slow</h3>
<p>Good thing is was a passion project, because the progress was
  <strong>really slow</strong>
  at the start.</p>

<p>After 4 months of creating a weekly video, I had 50 subs. But that was okay, because I was having fun making them.</p>

<h3 id="something-happened">Something happened</h3>
<p>And after those first four months, things started to pick up. I don’t know what changed, but more and more people started discovering my videos.</p>

<p>And since they started picking up, they haven’t slowed down!</p>

<h3 id="where-things-are-now">Where things are now</h3>
<p>“Now” is probably the wrong way to put it, because I doubt I’ll be updating this regularly, but as of July 24, 2018 I have
  <strong>over 25,000 subs</strong>
  and
  <strong>over 1.3 million total views</strong>.</p>

<p>That totally blows my mind. So if you’re one of those people who’ve watched a video or who’ve taken the time to sub,
  <strong>a very big thank you!</strong>
</p>

